{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh chicken into it. Set aside. Place garlic and ginger into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add coconut milk, soy sauce, coriander, chilli flakes, 1 teaspoon of the salt, 2 tablespoons of the turmeric and curry leaves (optional) and combine <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer into bowl with chicken and stir to combine. Cover and place into refrigerator overnight. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh mirin into it. Add Sriracha sauce and brown sugar, then stir to combine and set aside.","Line a large plate with paper towel and set aside. Place a shallow bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh flour into it. Add remaining 1 teaspoon salt and remaining 2 teaspoons turmeric into bowl and stir to combine. Set aside.","Place a large saucepan over medium heat and add enough oil to cover chicken. Bring oil to 165°C. To check oil temperature, drop a small cube of bread into oil; it should turn golden brown in 15-20 seconds. Keep your oil at this temperature while frying.","Remove chicken winglets from marinade and coat in flour mixture. Working in batches, fry chicken for 15-20 minutes, turning until cooked, crispy and golden. Transfer onto prepared plate to drain. Serve warm with reserved Sriracha mixture."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1000 - 1200 g chicken winglets (see Tips)","3 garlic cloves","3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","165 g coconut milk","2 tsp soy sauce","2 tsp ground coriander","1 tsp dried chilli flakes","2 tsp salt","2 ½ tbsp ground turmeric","4 - 5 sprigs fresh curry leaves (optional)","80 g mirin","3 tbsp Sriracha sauce","2 tbsp brown sugar","150 g plain flour","1500 g vegetable oil, for frying"]}],"id":"r238983","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-5KW6fWai5v8\/XZadXV9whwI\/AAAAAAAAgbA\/rvTc7nCGIQMEk3dkRm1R4FQYToa959YjgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_9m